1
00:00:04,404 --> 00:00:06,244
(Previously)
I have something to give you, Hia.

2
00:00:07,607 --> 00:00:09,642
You've given me so many things already.

3
00:00:10,493 --> 00:00:12,762
It's time I give you something in return.

4
00:00:18,802 --> 00:00:19,919
How thoughtful of you.

5
00:00:26,643 --> 00:00:27,961
Tonight is our last night.

6
00:00:30,363 --> 00:00:32,163
Wanna play Maruko?
(Thai slang for having sex)

7
00:00:42,980 --> 00:00:43,980
Hia...

8
00:00:46,813 --> 00:00:47,881
Wanna shower together?

9
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:53,135
Sure.

10
00:01:21,131 --> 00:01:22,131
Hey, baby.

11
00:01:24,534 --> 00:01:25,602
Don't call me 'baby'.

12
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:28,605
It makes me feel so awkward.

13
00:01:30,490 --> 00:01:32,351
If I'm a little mouse... (Baby in Thai
is "Noo" which also mean a mouse)

14
00:01:32,375 --> 00:01:33,375
How big is a buffalo?

15
00:01:34,961 --> 00:01:35,961
As big as...

16
00:01:38,002 --> 00:01:38,949
This!

17
00:01:38,949 --> 00:01:39,949
Hey!

18
00:01:41,726 --> 00:01:42,726
I'm sorry.

19
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,640
I don't like that at all.

20
00:01:49,125 --> 00:01:50,810
Try calling me 'baby' again.

21
00:01:52,412 --> 00:01:53,514
Baby.

22
00:01:55,669 --> 00:01:56,951
Again.

23
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,320
Baby.

24
00:02:01,888 --> 00:02:02,530
Louder.

25
00:02:02,530 --> 00:02:03,030
Baby!

26
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:03,530
Hey!

27
00:02:03,973 --> 00:02:04,973
Remember this.

28
00:02:05,725 --> 00:02:07,327
Don't raise your voice at me again.

29
00:02:08,127 --> 00:02:09,127
You have no right.

30
00:02:16,202 --> 00:02:17,604
Can you call me 'baby' again?

31
00:02:18,371 --> 00:02:19,923
Just one more time, please?

32
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,845
My boyfriend is a bit weird.

33
00:02:28,448 --> 00:02:29,482
But he's cute.

34
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:54,173
Hia.

35
00:02:56,726 --> 00:02:57,810
I'm hungry.

36
00:03:03,333 --> 00:03:04,333
Let's go eat.

37
00:03:05,051 --> 00:03:06,051
Yeah.

38
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:13,293
I'm sleepy, but I'm also hungry.

39
00:03:31,327 --> 00:03:32,327
Wait a second.

40
00:04:15,204 --> 00:04:16,406
Go put some clothes on.

41
00:04:39,879 --> 00:04:41,359
Or I won't be able to control myself.

42
00:04:54,410 --> 00:04:56,479
When did you buy these matching shirts?

43
00:04:57,647 --> 00:05:00,083
Whenever I wanted because I have money.

44
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:02,134
Right.

45
00:05:03,252 --> 00:05:04,252
I'm kidding.

46
00:05:05,676 --> 00:05:07,562
I bought them when you went to buy shoes.

47
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:12,161
I knew they'd look good on you.

48
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:18,251
What should we eat tonight?

49
00:05:19,535 --> 00:05:20,853
A beachside beer garden.

50
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:33,449
Speaking of beer, it reminds me of our bar.

51
00:05:37,286 --> 00:05:39,006
We should be able to open next week, right?

52
00:05:50,049 --> 00:05:51,451
Who said we're opening next week?

53
00:05:52,251 --> 00:05:53,891
We need to find an auspicious date first.

54
00:05:54,570 --> 00:05:56,172
Opening a business requires good timing.

55
00:05:57,724 --> 00:05:59,184
And we need a housewarming blessing.
(Buddhist tradition before opening a shop)

56
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:01,094
So we won't run into any more bad luck.

57
00:06:05,048 --> 00:06:06,048
Okay.

58
00:06:17,443 --> 00:06:19,563
Since we're looking for a
date for opening the bar...

59
00:06:20,530 --> 00:06:22,050
Should we look for a wedding date too?

60
00:06:25,284 --> 00:06:27,086
But we're already married.

61
00:06:29,772 --> 00:06:30,840
Since when?

62
00:06:32,608 --> 00:06:34,894
Since you put this ring on my finger.

63
00:06:38,081 --> 00:06:39,561
Then let's go to the district office.

64
00:06:40,850 --> 00:06:42,168
Let's register our marriage.

65
00:06:42,935 --> 00:06:44,253
Don't skip steps.

66
00:06:45,888 --> 00:06:47,573
You have to ask my dad for my hand first.

67
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:50,242
Sure.

68
00:07:05,324 --> 00:07:06,609
We can go as soon as we're free.

69
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:11,571
How serious are you? [Famous Thai lyrics]

70
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:14,928
How serious do you want
me to be? [Famous Thai lyrics]

71
00:07:26,679 --> 00:07:27,930
You're so adorable.

72
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:43,500
"ChermChey"
(Episode 10)

73
00:09:07,813 --> 00:09:08,813
Congratulations.

74
00:09:09,248 --> 00:09:10,248
Thank you.

75
00:09:11,484 --> 00:09:12,285
Hello, Dad.

76
00:09:12,485 --> 00:09:13,485
Hello.

77
00:09:13,853 --> 00:09:15,213
Is there anything I can help with?

78
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:17,173
Take a look inside.

79
00:09:25,214 --> 00:09:26,214
Hey there.

80
00:09:27,283 --> 00:09:28,367
Where is everyone else?

81
00:09:29,802 --> 00:09:30,970
They should be here soon.

82
00:09:31,687 --> 00:09:33,639
Oh, congratulations, by the way.

83
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,241
Thanks.

84
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:37,043
Has anyone else arrived yet?

85
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,528
Just P'Lit and Nine.

86
00:09:40,963 --> 00:09:41,963
Oh gosh.

87
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,399
P' Ton overslept.

88
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:45,201
We almost didn't make it.

89
00:09:45,735 --> 00:09:46,519
As usual.

90
00:09:46,569 --> 00:09:47,370
Yeah.

91
00:09:47,371 --> 00:09:49,288
Let's go help inside.

92
00:09:57,847 --> 00:09:58,847
Hia.

93
00:09:59,365 --> 00:10:00,883
How is it over there? Is it done?

94
00:10:01,484 --> 00:10:02,285
It's done.

95
00:10:02,368 --> 00:10:03,448
Has the master arrived yet?

96
00:10:04,370 --> 00:10:05,370
He should be here soon.

97
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:07,123
Where are your friends?

98
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:10,242
Just Ton and Aiyaret left.

99
00:10:12,128 --> 00:10:12,928
Oh.

100
00:10:12,929 --> 00:10:14,680
Hey, I'm here, my friend!

101
00:10:15,164 --> 00:10:16,164
I'm here!

102
00:10:16,482 --> 00:10:17,482
In.

103
00:10:18,451 --> 00:10:19,451
The master is here.

104
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:20,535
Hurry, everyone!

105
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:22,455
Go wait inside.

106
00:10:22,571 --> 00:10:24,498
Erng and I will welcome the master.

107
00:10:24,499 --> 00:10:24,999
Okay.

108
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:25,999
Okay.

109
00:10:26,409 --> 00:10:27,409
Let's go, Erng.

110
00:10:27,727 --> 00:10:28,727
Okay.

111
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:15,007
The shop looks beautiful.

112
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:20,212
I'm glad to perform the
opening ceremony today.

113
00:11:21,447 --> 00:11:23,025
By the way, what's the name of the shop?

114
00:11:23,049 --> 00:11:24,250
It's ChermChey, Master.

115
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:30,098
ChermChey.

116
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:33,008
Where does that name come from?

117
00:11:33,809 --> 00:11:37,246
It's a combination of my
name and my boyfriend's.

118
00:11:41,734 --> 00:11:43,369
Your boyfriend is quite cute.

119
00:11:48,007 --> 00:11:49,925
Where should we start?

120
00:11:50,159 --> 00:11:51,410
Upstairs, Master.

121
00:11:53,479 --> 00:11:54,479
Ah.

122
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:56,132
Let's begin then.

123
00:11:56,766 --> 00:11:57,766
Yes, sir.

124
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:01,887
Oh! Master!

125
00:12:02,121 --> 00:12:03,121
Master!

126
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:04,806
It was just a joke.

127
00:12:06,048 --> 00:12:07,138
Oh.

128
00:12:08,109 --> 00:12:09,629
Sathu.

129
00:12:58,596 --> 00:12:59,616
Erng.

130
00:13:00,593 --> 00:13:01,593
I'm so hot.

131
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:09,287
Are you possessed?

132
00:13:46,175 --> 00:13:48,894
May your business prosper
and be highly successful.

133
00:13:49,929 --> 00:13:51,130
Thank you, Master.

134
00:13:53,482 --> 00:13:54,283
See?

135
00:13:54,366 --> 00:13:55,366
That wasn't so hard.

136
00:13:55,935 --> 00:13:56,719
Wow.

137
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,053
I'm completely drenched in sweat.

138
00:13:58,654 --> 00:13:59,889
Well, everything is done.

139
00:14:00,489 --> 00:14:01,490
I shall take my leave.

140
00:14:02,691 --> 00:14:03,893
Sathu.

141
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,480
Master!

142
00:14:09,615 --> 00:14:10,615
You forgot your bag.

143
00:14:42,565 --> 00:14:43,565
Thank you.

144
00:15:13,245 --> 00:15:14,325
It's good to get some rest.

145
00:15:14,847 --> 00:15:16,248
You barely slept last night.

146
00:15:17,049 --> 00:15:19,001
And you've been running
around since morning.

147
00:15:23,973 --> 00:15:25,891
No need to rush or compete.

148
00:15:29,328 --> 00:15:30,763
Just being together is enough.

149
00:15:57,172 --> 00:15:57,923
Hey!

150
00:15:57,924 --> 00:16:00,442
How did you get in? I locked the door!

151
00:16:00,643 --> 00:16:01,843
You're not fast enough for me.

152
00:16:03,626 --> 00:16:04,860
Hia!

153
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:06,862
You little rascal.

154
00:16:10,369 --> 00:16:11,170
I'm not letting you go.

155
00:16:11,170 --> 00:16:12,170
You won't let go?

156
00:16:15,658 --> 00:16:16,818
Is this how you want to play?

157
00:16:18,424 --> 00:16:20,000
Is this what you want?

158
00:16:21,175 --> 00:16:22,175
Yeah.

159
00:16:22,348 --> 00:16:23,582
You want to do this?

160
00:16:23,952 --> 00:16:24,952
Yeah.

161
00:16:28,170 --> 00:16:29,722
Today is Sunday the 18th.

162
00:16:30,806 --> 00:16:31,806
An even day.

163
00:16:33,092 --> 00:16:34,092
As agreed,

164
00:16:34,643 --> 00:16:35,643
you do even days,

165
00:16:36,295 --> 00:16:37,363
and I do odd days.

166
00:16:38,814 --> 00:16:39,882
Today is an even day.

167
00:16:41,450 --> 00:16:42,450
So it's your turn.

168
00:16:44,603 --> 00:16:45,603
Really?

169
00:16:46,772 --> 00:16:48,207
Did I get the days mixed up?

170
00:16:49,408 --> 00:16:50,408
I'm sorry.

171
00:16:51,443 --> 00:16:52,843
Then come here and let me bite you.

172
00:16:54,646 --> 00:16:58,878
May all sentient beings,
partners in suffering...

173
00:16:59,357 --> 00:17:01,649
Please save me!

174
00:17:03,255 --> 00:17:04,763
Are you praying for mercy,

175
00:17:05,385 --> 00:17:07,000
or do you want me to punish you?

176
00:17:09,445 --> 00:17:11,330
Please have mercy on me!

177
00:20:16,365 --> 00:20:17,365
Hia!

178
00:20:18,089 --> 00:20:19,484
Why is my bedsheet stained?

179
00:20:19,935 --> 00:20:20,652
I didn't mean to.

180
00:20:20,653 --> 00:20:22,287
Shut up!

181
00:20:23,522 --> 00:20:25,123
We can wash it tomorrow, Erng.

182
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:27,009
Go wash it right now.

183
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:28,960
I'll wash it tomorrow.

184
00:20:29,294 --> 00:20:30,612
I already changed it for you.

185
00:20:32,014 --> 00:20:33,014
Go wash it.

186
00:20:37,970 --> 00:20:39,944
We can just use the black one for now.

187
00:20:40,854 --> 00:20:41,887
It's the same thing.

188
00:20:41,888 --> 00:20:43,671
I want to use the pink one.

189
00:20:43,672 --> 00:20:44,543
I don't care.

190
00:20:44,543 --> 00:20:45,543
Goodnight.

191
00:20:46,762 --> 00:20:47,762
I'm sleeping.

192
00:20:47,963 --> 00:20:48,963
I'm not getting up.

193
00:20:49,648 --> 00:20:50,648
You're not getting up?

194
00:20:51,049 --> 00:20:52,049
I'm going to sleep.

195
00:20:53,285 --> 00:20:54,285
Get up.

196
00:20:54,770 --> 00:20:56,204
Are you going to wash it or not?

197
00:20:56,488 --> 00:20:58,173
Not now. I'm sleepy.

198
00:20:58,807 --> 00:20:59,608
Suddenly feel sleepy huh?

199
00:20:59,808 --> 00:21:01,126
Go wash it right now!

200
00:21:03,211 --> 00:21:04,211
I'm already asleep.

201
00:21:04,529 --> 00:21:05,314
Oh, wow.

202
00:21:05,315 --> 00:21:06,415
Leave me alone.

203
00:21:06,565 --> 00:21:08,445
I guess you're not afraid
of your wife anymore.

204
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:10,719
Hey.

205
00:21:10,852 --> 00:21:11,852
Get up.

206
00:21:12,054 --> 00:21:13,121
Go do the laundry.

207
00:21:13,889 --> 00:21:14,889
Wait.

208
00:21:15,490 --> 00:21:16,490
Go wash it.

209
00:21:19,561 --> 00:21:21,129
Hia, go do the laundry right now.

210
00:21:21,647 --> 00:21:22,647
I'll do it tomorrow.

211
00:21:22,881 --> 00:21:23,932
I want it done today.

212
00:21:24,283 --> 00:21:25,600
Tomorrow is fine, Erng.

213
00:21:25,767 --> 00:21:27,767
If you don't wash it, what
am I going to sleep on?

214
00:21:28,253 --> 00:21:31,440
I already put a new black one on for you.

215
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:33,374
Isn't it the same?

216
00:21:33,608 --> 00:21:35,410
I want the pink one. I like pink.

217
00:21:37,763 --> 00:21:38,763
I'm going to sleep.

218
00:21:41,650 --> 00:21:43,485
You've gotten so stubborn lately.

219
00:21:44,169 --> 00:21:45,438
Hey, what are you doing?

220
00:21:45,439 --> 00:21:46,439
I'm not going.

221
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:47,354
Ouch!

222
00:21:47,354 --> 00:21:47,854
Erng!

223
00:21:47,854 --> 00:21:48,354
Wash it!

224
00:21:48,354 --> 00:21:48,974
Erng, I'm not playing.

225
00:21:49,007 --> 00:21:50,101
You want a piece of me, Erng?

226
00:21:50,125 --> 00:21:51,419
You're the one who wants it, huh?

227
00:21:51,443 --> 00:21:52,094
You want a piece?

228
00:21:52,095 --> 00:21:53,412
You want to go? Get up!

229
00:21:53,962 --> 00:21:54,763
Get up!

230
00:21:54,846 --> 00:21:55,846
Go wash the sheets.

231
00:21:56,014 --> 00:21:57,291
Go wash the sheets!

232
00:22:02,540 --> 00:22:03,151
Hia!

233
00:22:03,151 --> 00:22:04,151
You want more?

234
00:22:04,633 --> 00:22:05,867
I told you to wash the sheets!

235
00:22:06,859 --> 00:22:08,859
You really want to mess with me, Erng?

236
00:22:12,647 --> 00:22:13,847
You're not going to wash them?

237
00:22:16,230 --> 00:22:17,230
You want some of this?

238
00:22:17,496 --> 00:22:19,121
Are you going to wash the sheets?

239
00:22:19,122 --> 00:22:20,202
Are you going to wash them?

240
00:22:20,362 --> 00:22:21,559
Fine, fine! I'll go!

241
00:22:23,043 --> 00:22:24,525
Hurry up!

242
00:22:25,004 --> 00:22:26,819
Move it!

243
00:22:27,679 --> 00:22:28,290
I'm going!

244
00:22:28,290 --> 00:22:29,005
Hurry up!

245
00:22:29,006 --> 00:22:30,246
Can I at least put on my shoes?

246
00:22:40,575 --> 00:22:41,360
Hey!

247
00:22:41,526 --> 00:22:42,526
Geez.

248
00:22:43,495 --> 00:22:45,247
Wash them quick. I like pink.

249
00:22:54,573 --> 00:22:57,245
Mirror, mirror on the wall...

250
00:22:58,203 --> 00:23:02,364
Who is the fairest of them all?

251
00:23:03,331 --> 00:23:04,683
It's Erng, of course!

252
00:23:06,651 --> 00:23:09,204
What? I didn't say anything.

253
00:23:10,605 --> 00:23:11,605
Then who said it?

254
00:23:12,290 --> 00:23:13,644
Is this really your house?

255
00:23:13,645 --> 00:23:14,645
Of course.

256
00:23:16,361 --> 00:23:17,361
It's so spacious.

257
00:23:18,647 --> 00:23:20,029
This is my dad's house.

258
00:23:20,030 --> 00:23:23,168
My house is around here, close by.
Not too far.

259
00:23:29,374 --> 00:23:31,126
Do I look presentable?

260
00:23:32,127 --> 00:23:35,614
Any more presentable and
you'd be wearing monk robes.

261
00:23:36,281 --> 00:23:37,849
I really want to smack your mouth.

262
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,135
You're always so brave about hitting me.

263
00:23:40,652 --> 00:23:42,254
You've gotten so bold.

264
00:23:45,173 --> 00:23:46,173
Erng.

265
00:23:47,212 --> 00:23:48,244
When we grow old...

266
00:23:48,962 --> 00:23:50,877
Can we be Uncle In and Aunt Erng...

267
00:23:51,643 --> 00:23:54,444
living here together?

268
00:23:55,534 --> 00:23:56,534
Sure.

269
00:23:58,453 --> 00:23:59,454
Do you want me to?

270
00:24:00,722 --> 00:24:02,841
If you haven't left me by then...

271
00:24:04,493 --> 00:24:05,961
I'd love for you to live with me.

272
00:24:09,731 --> 00:24:10,731
I'm blushing.

273
00:24:11,199 --> 00:24:13,768
Erng Erng just asked me to
spend the rest of my life with her.

274
00:24:16,004 --> 00:24:17,004
Huh?

275
00:24:17,205 --> 00:24:18,690
You're the one who started it, Hia.

276
00:24:29,534 --> 00:24:30,770
Hello, Father.

277
00:24:30,771 --> 00:24:32,170
Hey there.

278
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:43,448
Dad, what is there to eat?

279
00:24:43,615 --> 00:24:44,683
I'm starving.

280
00:24:45,167 --> 00:24:47,719
Wow, you just got here and
you're already asking for food.

281
00:24:47,969 --> 00:24:49,855
Go get him some water first.

282
00:24:50,205 --> 00:24:52,007
Fine, I'm going to the restroom first.

283
00:24:52,174 --> 00:24:53,174
I really need to go.

284
00:24:55,210 --> 00:24:56,244
Do whatever you want.

285
00:24:57,095 --> 00:24:58,930
But I really have to go, Dad!

286
00:25:00,649 --> 00:25:01,649
Whoa.

287
00:25:01,850 --> 00:25:02,850
Huh?

288
00:25:04,821 --> 00:25:06,821
Ouch, that hurts!

289
00:25:07,055 --> 00:25:08,564
Go, go. Go wherever you want.

290
00:25:10,383 --> 00:25:11,092
Hey, In.

291
00:25:11,359 --> 00:25:14,679
I'll get you some water.
Wait here for a bit.

292
00:25:15,247 --> 00:25:16,247
Yes, sir.

293
00:25:31,046 --> 00:25:32,046
I bet...

294
00:25:33,401 --> 00:25:34,678
Erng Erng's dad...

295
00:25:35,157 --> 00:25:37,569
decorated the house like a
princess, just like Erng Erng.

296
00:25:47,412 --> 00:25:48,412
Holy crap.

297
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:51,199
Whoa.

298
00:25:52,133 --> 00:25:53,133
You must be In, right?

299
00:25:53,935 --> 00:25:54,935
Hello, Mother.

300
00:25:55,253 --> 00:25:56,253
Hello.

301
00:25:56,815 --> 00:26:00,091
You're much handsomer
in person than in the photos.

302
00:26:00,775 --> 00:26:03,211
Thank you. You're very
beautiful too, Mother.

303
00:26:03,562 --> 00:26:04,562
Thank you.

304
00:26:06,248 --> 00:26:07,799
I brought some fruit for you.

305
00:26:08,683 --> 00:26:09,768
I hope you enjoy it.

306
00:26:10,335 --> 00:26:11,335
Thank you, dear.

307
00:26:22,931 --> 00:26:23,431
Have a seat.

308
00:26:23,431 --> 00:26:24,431
Thank you.

309
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,651
Oh, dear!

310
00:26:27,168 --> 00:26:28,403
Sit on the chair, sweetie.

311
00:26:28,853 --> 00:26:29,853
Up there.

312
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:37,845
Oh, right.

313
00:26:46,771 --> 00:26:47,771
I'm sorry.

314
00:26:48,223 --> 00:26:50,892
I'm just a bit nervous.

315
00:26:51,643 --> 00:26:53,295
That's a bit hard to swallow.

316
00:27:01,803 --> 00:27:02,804
It wasn't me.

317
00:27:06,241 --> 00:27:07,241
It was me, dear.

318
00:27:08,326 --> 00:27:09,326
Aren't you embarrassed?

319
00:27:09,611 --> 00:27:12,964
And where did Khem go, Dad?
Why did he leave In all alone?

320
00:27:13,214 --> 00:27:14,282
Khem went to the restroom.

321
00:27:14,733 --> 00:27:17,344
In, dear, Khem told me...

322
00:27:17,345 --> 00:27:19,795
that you like your
food on the spicier side.

323
00:27:19,796 --> 00:27:22,153
So I made a few spicy dishes for you.

324
00:27:22,154 --> 00:27:25,727
But I'm not sure if you'll like them.

325
00:27:26,761 --> 00:27:27,612
I can eat anything, really.

326
00:27:27,762 --> 00:27:28,880
Except for vegetables.

327
00:27:29,047 --> 00:27:30,281
Ah, that's good.

328
00:27:30,732 --> 00:27:32,000
The princess is here!

329
00:27:44,785 --> 00:27:47,048
Dad, I told you to change the sofa.

330
00:27:48,092 --> 00:27:49,326
Do you think my legs are tiny?

331
00:27:51,002 --> 00:27:52,320
Isn't this sofa too small, Dad?

332
00:27:52,570 --> 00:27:53,614
You should buy a new one next time.

333
00:27:53,615 --> 00:27:54,615
Right.

334
00:27:55,090 --> 00:27:56,491
I look so tiny right now.

335
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:01,529
Did Dad talk behind my back to Hia?

336
00:28:01,763 --> 00:28:04,132
Oh, who would talk behind your back?

337
00:28:04,966 --> 00:28:06,509
Is there anything good to say about you?

338
00:28:06,510 --> 00:28:07,510
Wow.

339
00:28:07,886 --> 00:28:08,886
Plenty, Dad.

340
00:28:09,688 --> 00:28:10,889
I'm pretty, right, Hia?

341
00:28:11,172 --> 00:28:12,172
Right, Hia?

342
00:28:12,691 --> 00:28:14,042
Erng Erng is pretty, right?

343
00:28:14,843 --> 00:28:16,270
Yes, you are, N'Khem.

344
00:28:16,294 --> 00:28:17,762
Who taught you to call me that?

345
00:28:17,929 --> 00:28:18,929
Oh.

346
00:28:19,130 --> 00:28:23,168
Sorry, I was just following
your parents' lead.

347
00:28:23,802 --> 00:28:24,919
Just so you know, Khem.

348
00:28:25,653 --> 00:28:27,733
Your husband has already
been bought by Mom and Dad.

349
00:28:36,531 --> 00:28:37,585
Who wants to be a millionaire?

350
00:28:37,586 --> 00:28:38,086
I do!

351
00:28:38,133 --> 00:28:38,566
I do!

352
00:28:38,566 --> 00:28:39,367
He's all mine now.

353
00:28:39,451 --> 00:28:40,451
Stop.

354
00:28:40,573 --> 00:28:41,573
I'm not playing anymore.

355
00:28:42,203 --> 00:28:43,203
Dad.

356
00:28:44,055 --> 00:28:46,374
I'm hungry. Let's go eat.

357
00:28:49,611 --> 00:28:50,611
Mom.

358
00:28:51,246 --> 00:28:53,406
When you can't get your way
with Dad, you turn to Mom.

359
00:28:53,481 --> 00:28:55,200
Well, Mom's cooking is the best.

360
00:28:55,734 --> 00:28:56,974
Dad's cooking is just mediocre.

361
00:28:57,452 --> 00:28:58,946
Then go eat that mediocre food, kiddo.

362
00:28:58,970 --> 00:29:00,120
Should I let you starve instead?

363
00:29:00,121 --> 00:29:00,621
Go on.

364
00:29:00,621 --> 00:29:01,121
Hey!

365
00:29:01,122 --> 00:29:02,122
Go, go eat.

366
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:03,640
Go.

367
00:29:04,125 --> 00:29:05,210
Go eat.

368
00:29:05,693 --> 00:29:06,693
Come on.

369
00:29:13,651 --> 00:29:14,651
Hey.

370
00:29:15,687 --> 00:29:16,687
Let's eat.

371
00:29:16,721 --> 00:29:17,721
Yes, Father.

372
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:20,210
If you say yes, then get up.

373
00:29:21,292 --> 00:29:22,494
Going right now, sir.

374
00:29:35,723 --> 00:29:37,208
If I marry Erng...

375
00:29:37,442 --> 00:29:38,893
will I get all of this?

376
00:29:41,446 --> 00:29:42,680
Wait until I die first.

377
00:29:43,014 --> 00:29:45,133
I'll leave it all to you, son-in-law.

378
00:29:46,334 --> 00:29:47,641
I'm definitely marrying her then.

379
00:29:47,642 --> 00:29:48,142
Good, good.

380
00:29:48,203 --> 00:29:49,203
I'm not marrying him.

381
00:29:50,889 --> 00:29:51,889
What?

382
00:29:53,575 --> 00:29:54,575
Why not?

383
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:57,011
I'm afraid of black magic.

384
00:29:58,079 --> 00:29:59,079
Nonsense.

385
00:29:59,848 --> 00:30:01,483
If you're not sleeping yet, stay here.

386
00:30:02,133 --> 00:30:03,133
I'm going to bed.

387
00:30:03,251 --> 00:30:05,211
Make sure to bring the
clothes down from the car.

388
00:30:05,487 --> 00:30:07,288
Khem is just sulking, son-in-law.

389
00:30:07,722 --> 00:30:09,290
You can check on these tomorrow.

390
00:30:09,841 --> 00:30:10,841
Yes, Father-in-law.

391
00:30:11,009 --> 00:30:13,411
I'll go make it up to him now.

392
00:30:13,895 --> 00:30:15,168
Go ahead, son-in-law.

393
00:30:15,169 --> 00:30:16,169
Geez.

394
00:30:16,447 --> 00:30:18,527
What's with this father-in-law
and son-in-law stuff?

395
00:30:19,367 --> 00:30:20,300
I can't stand this.

396
00:30:20,301 --> 00:30:23,008
And just so you know, I'm not sulking.

397
00:30:23,009 --> 00:30:24,439
Hey, Dad.

398
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:28,797
Who's Khem? I'm Erng
Erng, the prettiest girl.

399
00:30:31,957 --> 00:30:33,388
I'll excuse myself now.

400
00:30:33,389 --> 00:30:35,062
Go ahead, son.

401
00:30:35,828 --> 00:30:36,828
Erng.

402
00:31:04,445 --> 00:31:05,445
Erng, dear.

403
00:31:06,281 --> 00:31:08,681
I've been looking at these
amulets until my eyes are blurry.

404
00:31:10,001 --> 00:31:11,202
Isn't that how it should be?

405
00:31:12,770 --> 00:31:14,973
But why call each other
father-in-law and son-in-law?

406
00:31:16,174 --> 00:31:17,174
Well...

407
00:31:17,492 --> 00:31:19,010
Because your dad is my father-in-law.

408
00:31:20,495 --> 00:31:21,613
Whatever makes you happy.

409
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:24,532
I'm just glad to see you two getting along.

410
00:31:34,959 --> 00:31:35,959
Erng.

411
00:31:39,847 --> 00:31:41,366
Are you showered and ready for bed?

412
00:31:42,283 --> 00:31:43,851
When did you take a shower?

413
00:31:47,722 --> 00:31:49,641
While you were busy examining your amulets.

414
00:31:50,575 --> 00:31:51,575
Was I...

415
00:31:51,912 --> 00:31:53,928
examining them until this late?

416
00:31:54,362 --> 00:31:55,362
Yes.

417
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:57,953
If it weren't this late, I
wouldn't have called you.

418
00:32:05,773 --> 00:32:08,893
Taking a shower now,
the water must be freezing.

419
00:32:10,128 --> 00:32:13,965
Don't worry, my house has a water heater.

420
00:32:40,608 --> 00:32:41,608
Whoa!

421
00:32:44,071 --> 00:32:45,071
I...

422
00:32:45,125 --> 00:32:46,467
I I'm frightened.

423
00:32:48,095 --> 00:32:50,507
Why did you jump like that?

424
00:32:50,508 --> 00:32:51,607
I'm scared of ghosts.

425
00:32:51,608 --> 00:32:53,975
Oh my god, you scared me too.

426
00:32:56,691 --> 00:32:57,691
Can I...

427
00:32:59,036 --> 00:33:00,528
rest my head on your lap?

428
00:33:00,962 --> 00:33:01,962
Hmm?

429
00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:03,647
Sure.

430
00:33:06,451 --> 00:33:07,735
You're the sweetest.

431
00:33:09,087 --> 00:33:11,205
Seems like we need to
buy a new sofa next time.

432
00:33:11,289 --> 00:33:12,373
This one is so small.

433
00:33:17,045 --> 00:33:18,357
Should we turn it off?

434
00:33:18,836 --> 00:33:20,014
And go to bed properly?

435
00:33:21,082 --> 00:33:23,780
No, I still want to watch.

436
00:33:24,690 --> 00:33:26,575
I want to see how it ends.

437
00:33:28,523 --> 00:33:29,523
Okay.

438
00:33:30,241 --> 00:33:31,693
Then just lie on my lap.

439
00:33:33,249 --> 00:33:34,531
Erng.

440
00:33:35,715 --> 00:33:36,715
Yes?

441
00:33:41,402 --> 00:33:43,054
When I said I wanted to marry you...

442
00:33:45,089 --> 00:33:46,324
I wasn't joking.

443
00:33:57,135 --> 00:33:59,520
You're not proposing during
a horror movie, are you?

444
00:34:00,371 --> 00:34:01,371
No.

445
00:34:05,209 --> 00:34:06,644
I won't propose right now.

446
00:34:08,613 --> 00:34:10,448
But when the time actually comes...

447
00:34:12,200 --> 00:34:14,001
please don't say no.

448
00:34:18,005 --> 00:34:20,758
I'll be waiting for that day.

449
00:34:24,645 --> 00:34:25,645
You're the sweetest.

450
00:34:27,165 --> 00:34:28,883
And you're the best in the world.

451
00:34:31,853 --> 00:34:32,853
I love you.

452
00:34:34,205 --> 00:34:35,239
I love you too.

453
00:34:40,044 --> 00:34:42,046
Saying "I love you" during a horror movie.

454
00:34:47,085 --> 00:34:49,445
Want to make our own movie, Erng?

455
00:34:50,371 --> 00:34:51,371
I'll show you how.

456
00:34:54,609 --> 00:34:56,327
And who are you playing with? Tell me.

457
00:34:57,011 --> 00:34:58,729
Whoever's lap I'm lying on.

458
00:35:00,681 --> 00:35:02,366
A change of scenery would be nice.

459
00:35:03,134 --> 00:35:05,414
We have to wake up early to
make merit with Dad tomorrow.

460
00:35:05,570 --> 00:35:06,570
In the morning.

461
00:35:07,054 --> 00:35:08,414
I'll definitely be able to get up.

462
00:35:10,208 --> 00:35:12,043
Then you'll have to drag me along.

463
00:35:15,963 --> 00:35:17,648
Let's go do it then.

464
00:35:20,251 --> 00:35:21,251
Ow!

465
00:35:21,919 --> 00:35:22,720
Right now?

466
00:35:22,770 --> 00:35:23,571
Well, you won't get up.

467
00:35:23,721 --> 00:35:25,761
If we're going to do it,
let's go somewhere better.

468
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:54,180
P'Nai and N' Erng.

469
00:35:54,611 --> 00:35:58,143
Do you think our husbands
will survive grocery shopping?

470
00:36:00,525 --> 00:36:03,211
I think my husband, In, is good at it.

471
00:36:03,528 --> 00:36:04,528
Hmm.

472
00:36:05,046 --> 00:36:08,399
Aiyaret is just as good at it,
you know.

473
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:10,885
Sis, can you not try to outdo me for once?

474
00:36:11,335 --> 00:36:12,854
I don't give In any credit.

475
00:36:12,970 --> 00:36:14,655
Even if he is my best friend.

476
00:36:15,239 --> 00:36:18,369
Hey, Erng, let me ask you something.

477
00:36:18,370 --> 00:36:19,754
How did you two meet?

478
00:36:19,755 --> 00:36:23,931
That monk friend of mine told
me a story so confusing, I'm lost.

479
00:36:24,482 --> 00:36:26,484
Can you tell us, or is it a secret?

480
00:36:27,168 --> 00:36:29,282
He really did make a mess of the story.

481
00:36:29,283 --> 00:36:32,203
Saying they met here and
there, it's all over the place.

482
00:36:32,204 --> 00:36:34,125
But it's not a secret.

483
00:36:36,811 --> 00:36:39,680
Then spill the beans, sweetie.

484
00:36:40,481 --> 00:36:43,734
Oh sis, calling me "sweetie"
just because you want to gossip.

485
00:36:46,170 --> 00:36:49,123
We met on a temple trip,
had a one-night stand...

486
00:36:49,523 --> 00:36:51,352
and then he confessed he liked me...

487
00:36:51,974 --> 00:36:53,961
before disappearing to
host a Kathina ceremony.

488
00:36:54,295 --> 00:36:55,079
A Kathina ceremony?

489
00:36:55,246 --> 00:36:56,331
Yeah, a Kathina ceremony.

490
00:36:56,332 --> 00:36:58,416
At first, I thought it was
just a one-night stand.

491
00:36:58,417 --> 00:37:01,977
But I didn't expect him to come back and make
my dream of having a real husband come true.

492
00:37:02,453 --> 00:37:03,454
What about you guys?

493
00:37:04,405 --> 00:37:05,806
How did everyone meet?

494
00:37:06,324 --> 00:37:07,324
Hmm...

495
00:37:08,092 --> 00:37:09,443
I don't really remember.

496
00:37:09,694 --> 00:37:11,245
But as far back as I can remember,

497
00:37:13,047 --> 00:37:16,932
P'Tonhon has always been in my life.

498
00:37:16,933 --> 00:37:18,573
Our houses were right next to each other.

499
00:37:19,003 --> 00:37:22,690
Yeah, his family claimed him
while he was still in his mother's womb.

500
00:37:23,291 --> 00:37:24,291
Wow.

501
00:37:25,693 --> 00:37:27,695
As for me, we were friends.

502
00:37:28,245 --> 00:37:32,482
Then you got drunk, and
Ai ended up devouring you.

503
00:37:33,850 --> 00:37:35,603
Right at the sofa in condo.

504
00:37:37,805 --> 00:37:40,691
But how do you know so much, Nine?

505
00:37:41,409 --> 00:37:44,137
That night, I passed out drunk.

506
00:37:44,138 --> 00:37:45,446
But I know everything.

507
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:48,366
Every single detail of what happened.

508
00:37:49,166 --> 00:37:51,402
And how did you find out?

509
00:37:51,602 --> 00:37:53,854
Nai told me everything.

510
00:37:54,405 --> 00:37:57,692
It's like he was proud of being devoured.

511
00:37:59,727 --> 00:38:00,727
And you...

512
00:38:01,012 --> 00:38:02,246
you and Lit.

513
00:38:04,882 --> 00:38:06,250
You kept it so quiet, you jerk.

514
00:38:06,968 --> 00:38:09,233
By the time we found
out, you were drunk with In.

515
00:38:09,234 --> 00:38:10,805
Drinking beer until you were wasted.

516
00:38:11,372 --> 00:38:14,241
I heard you threw a shoe
at your dad too, right?

517
00:38:16,610 --> 00:38:18,412
That's a private matter.

518
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:20,080
But we're friends!

519
00:38:20,815 --> 00:38:21,849
Spill the tea.

520
00:38:24,919 --> 00:38:25,919
It was nothing.

521
00:38:27,288 --> 00:38:28,968
Out of nowhere, Lit came up to talk to me.

522
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:30,925
Just making casual conversation.

523
00:38:32,009 --> 00:38:33,928
Next thing I knew...

524
00:38:35,012 --> 00:38:37,214
how did I end up with such a hot guy?

525
00:38:37,481 --> 00:38:38,481
Wow.

526
00:38:38,599 --> 00:38:39,099
Oh, please.

527
00:38:39,099 --> 00:38:40,099
Whoa.

528
00:38:40,851 --> 00:38:42,570
As for the day I went with In...

529
00:38:42,803 --> 00:38:44,288
there was a little misunderstanding.

530
00:38:45,289 --> 00:38:48,796
So I had to mark my territory.

531
00:38:48,797 --> 00:38:49,797
He's mine.

532
00:38:50,361 --> 00:38:51,529
Everybody hands off.

533
00:38:52,813 --> 00:38:53,813
Wow.

534
00:38:54,081 --> 00:38:55,081
Hmm.

535
00:38:55,366 --> 00:38:57,485
Nine is definitely the wildest one here.

536
00:39:00,171 --> 00:39:01,889
Are any of my friends actually normal?

537
00:39:02,006 --> 00:39:03,006
Seriously.

538
00:39:03,174 --> 00:39:05,242
But P'Ton is normal.

539
00:39:05,810 --> 00:39:06,810
Oh, please.

540
00:39:07,845 --> 00:39:09,647
I think he's the worst of them all.

541
00:39:10,531 --> 00:39:11,531
Everyone!

542
00:39:11,599 --> 00:39:14,251
Okay, one, two, three, cheers!

543
00:39:26,339 --> 00:39:31,023
(One year later)

544
00:39:38,809 --> 00:39:42,279
Erng, it's time to fulfill our vow.

545
00:39:48,719 --> 00:39:50,971
You're just looking
for an excuse to travel.

546
00:39:54,692 --> 00:39:55,692
Look.

547
00:39:56,561 --> 00:39:58,061
The essentials.

548
00:39:58,588 --> 00:40:00,198
So we have everything.

549
00:40:02,483 --> 00:40:03,684
Let's see what's in here.

550
00:40:04,001 --> 00:40:05,001
You already know.

551
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:21,452
That's enough. Why so many kisses?

552
00:40:21,641 --> 00:40:23,119
Or...

553
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:24,112
do you want me to kiss you somewhere else?

554
00:40:24,113 --> 00:40:25,206
Just try it.

555
00:40:25,445 --> 00:40:26,445
Come on.

556
00:40:29,761 --> 00:40:30,761
I'm leaving.

557
00:40:34,999 --> 00:40:35,999
Where are you going?

558
00:40:45,843 --> 00:40:46,843
Erng.

559
00:40:49,167 --> 00:40:50,167
Matching shirts.

560
00:40:51,346 --> 00:40:52,346
What do you think?

561
00:40:52,555 --> 00:40:53,835
Let's buy them to wear together.

562
00:40:54,558 --> 00:40:56,052
Sure.

563
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:59,206
But isn't it too much? We're
only going for a few days.

564
00:40:59,490 --> 00:41:02,159
Better to buy and not wear
than to want and not buy.

565
00:41:02,726 --> 00:41:04,161
I'm too tired to argue.

566
00:41:05,460 --> 00:41:06,460
Take it.

567
00:41:06,986 --> 00:41:08,048
I'll take them then.

568
00:41:08,883 --> 00:41:10,050
We'll take these two.

569
00:41:11,085 --> 00:41:13,804
No bag, please. I'll put
them in my shoulder bag.

570
00:41:15,439 --> 00:41:18,759
Are you sure you're not
checking other people out?

571
00:41:19,410 --> 00:41:20,694
I haven't even looked at anyone.

572
00:41:22,079 --> 00:41:23,279
I don't look at anyone else...

573
00:41:23,764 --> 00:41:25,132
since I got a fierce wife.

574
00:41:25,733 --> 00:41:26,733
Am I fierce?

575
00:41:26,884 --> 00:41:27,884
Very fierce.

576
00:41:28,085 --> 00:41:29,253
You beat me up without mercy.

577
00:41:29,453 --> 00:41:31,088
I think eight of my ribs are broken.

578
00:41:31,572 --> 00:41:33,492
Oh, please. You're the
one who's fierce with me.

579
00:41:34,124 --> 00:41:35,124
I'm calling the cops.

580
00:41:35,209 --> 00:41:36,689
You're crazy. I'm not talking to you.

581
00:42:08,125 --> 00:42:09,360
My wife is so cute.

582
00:42:11,161 --> 00:42:12,161
Look.

583
00:42:13,447 --> 00:42:14,848
There are seashells too.

584
00:42:15,683 --> 00:42:16,683
I'll buy them for you.

585
00:42:18,402 --> 00:42:19,403
Thanks.

586
00:42:21,805 --> 00:42:23,891
Let's keep shopping.

587
00:43:04,081 --> 00:43:05,081
Look.

588
00:43:05,249 --> 00:43:07,134
If I wear this hair clip to the market,

589
00:43:07,451 --> 00:43:08,602
will I get beaten up?

590
00:43:10,254 --> 00:43:11,839
If anyone dares to touch you,

591
00:43:12,323 --> 00:43:13,524
I'll protect you.

592
00:43:16,126 --> 00:43:18,245
I feel so small and safe with you.

593
00:43:20,681 --> 00:43:21,849
That's a good thing.

594
00:43:27,121 --> 00:43:29,089
Then I'll wear this
clip to fulfill our vow.

595
00:43:35,963 --> 00:43:37,848
I feel so lucky to have you.

596
00:43:39,566 --> 00:43:41,919
Saying "lucky" a million
times wouldn't be enough.

597
00:43:59,486 --> 00:44:01,605
I'm lucky to have you too.

598
00:44:35,572 --> 00:44:36,572
Aww.

599
00:44:43,163 --> 00:44:45,449
Last time I came here, I was so clueless.

600
00:44:46,133 --> 00:44:47,685
But this time, you have me.

601
00:44:49,370 --> 00:44:50,654
Your personal temple boy.

602
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:18,048
Wait for me here.

603
00:45:18,165 --> 00:45:19,165
I'll be right back.

604
00:45:57,004 --> 00:45:58,839
Where did you go?

605
00:46:00,891 --> 00:46:03,327
Go buy one of these for yourselves.

606
00:46:05,813 --> 00:46:07,733
This one makes your
husband love you like crazy.

607
00:46:08,165 --> 00:46:09,605
This one makes him totally obsessed.

608
00:46:10,334 --> 00:46:13,003
And this one makes him super handsome.

609
00:46:14,054 --> 00:46:16,974
I knew it. He totally scammed me.

610
00:46:20,527 --> 00:46:21,527
Let's take some picture.

611
00:46:26,166 --> 00:46:26,967
That's enough.

612
00:46:27,134 --> 00:46:28,919
I didn't mean to show off my husband.

613
00:46:30,001 --> 00:46:30,921
(Noknoinarak: My friend got a
husband and won't stop showing him off)

614
00:46:30,922 --> 00:46:32,882
But everyone still accuses
me of showing you off.

615
00:46:37,494 --> 00:46:39,012
Where are we going after this?

616
00:46:41,849 --> 00:46:42,849
Where do you want to go?

617
00:46:43,450 --> 00:46:45,947
A nice restaurant...

618
00:46:46,522 --> 00:46:47,721
Or street food?

619
00:46:48,405 --> 00:46:49,439
The latter sounds good.

620
00:46:51,241 --> 00:46:52,241
Then...

621
00:46:53,943 --> 00:46:56,007
Sausage and grilled clams.

622
00:46:59,483 --> 00:47:00,483
Dirty-minded!

623
00:47:02,052 --> 00:47:03,052
What's dirty about it?

624
00:47:03,113 --> 00:47:06,276
You're the one with the dirty
mind. Sausage is just sausage.

625
00:47:06,277 --> 00:47:08,692
And grilled clams are
just scallops on a skewer.

626
00:47:09,293 --> 00:47:11,094
I can't with you.

627
00:47:11,929 --> 00:47:13,084
Always so dirty-minded.

628
00:47:13,085 --> 00:47:14,085
Hey!

629
00:47:17,050 --> 00:47:18,050
Erng.

630
00:47:19,520 --> 00:47:20,520
Erng.

631
00:47:23,290 --> 00:47:24,383
You always pick on me.

632
00:47:24,384 --> 00:47:26,476
Go eat your sausage and
clams somewhere else.

633
00:47:26,477 --> 00:47:27,644
Don't talk to me anymore.

634
00:47:34,568 --> 00:47:35,568
Erng.

635
00:47:35,657 --> 00:47:36,657
If you pull away again...

636
00:47:36,999 --> 00:47:38,279
You won't get any sleep tonight.

637
00:47:54,288 --> 00:47:56,123
When we were praying earlier...

638
00:47:59,126 --> 00:48:01,295
I wished for us to be happy forever.

639
00:48:04,081 --> 00:48:05,081
I made a wish too.

640
00:48:06,133 --> 00:48:07,284
But I think...

641
00:48:08,368 --> 00:48:09,608
This temple is really powerful.

642
00:48:11,088 --> 00:48:12,088
Why?

643
00:48:13,774 --> 00:48:15,442
Because I'm already happy now.

644
00:48:17,010 --> 00:48:18,412
I just made the wish,

645
00:48:19,012 --> 00:48:20,247
and I'm already happy.

646
00:48:27,170 --> 00:48:28,405
Still as cheeky as ever.

647
00:48:30,173 --> 00:48:31,241
And do you like it?

648
00:48:35,012 --> 00:48:36,012
I love it.

649
00:48:38,999 --> 00:48:40,400
I think the world is strange.

650
00:48:42,402 --> 00:48:44,204
I don't even know how we ended up together.

651
00:48:45,689 --> 00:48:46,689
Yeah.

652
00:48:47,608 --> 00:48:49,293
Do you still believe in destiny?

653
00:48:51,928 --> 00:48:52,928
No.

654
00:48:53,721 --> 00:48:56,219
I think finding someone
you like isn't hard.

655
00:48:59,330 --> 00:49:00,969
Making it last is the hard part.

656
00:49:05,375 --> 00:49:06,927
Then you have to feed it with sausage.

657
00:49:11,648 --> 00:49:13,567
It feels like we're not
even on the same page.

658
00:49:30,005 --> 00:49:31,005
Let's go.

